Instances.Input.question: The man started to learn jogging, what was he hoping to do?
Instances.Input.answer_choices: fatigue, fitness, exhaustion, getting in shape, or injure himself
Instances.Input.explanation_1: Getting in shape is to work to have good, robust health; to become strong or fit. The man started to learn jogging; he was hoping to get in shape.  While jogging is a slow running below 6mph doesn’t get the stage of exhaustion as the man starting to learn jogging will be positive and will not hope of exhaustion. Better fitness is a result of continuous workouts. Fitness is not true as he has started to learn jogging. Injure himself is totally weird as no one wishes to harm himself. Fatigue is extreme tiredness resulting from mental or physical exertion or illness. Fatigue is not one hopes while learning jogging.
Instances.Input.explanation_2: Jogging is a kind of exercise that is usually designed to help one get in shape.
